Dialogs.Dialog: (I know！ I should invite Manaka for a trip to Hakone.)
Guess what, I won a travel prize again！
Really！？ Then, should we go to another school trip？
However, this time we are on our honeymoon！ We'll go on a domestic trip, two days and one night in Hakone！！
Rediscovering domestic honeymoons, 1 night and 2 days in Hakone.
Oh yeah！ By the way, Prez Tezuka will be in the next doubles match, right？
...Are you pretending you're not hearing me ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
The idea might be old, but I think it's better to go on a honeymoon after getting married...
Hmm... If you're not married, you can't be a newlywed... No, that's not it！
In the 30's of the Showa Era, honeymooners went to Hakone and to Atami.
It seems those places are tour spots for young people to visit once.
Then, you mean... it's just a trip with that theme？
I see... Then, maybe you want to save it for another time.
(I wonder if I surprised her too much.)
Umm, excuse me？ The thing we spoke about before...
If you think about it, it's just a trip to Hakone, right？
Whether it's like a honeymoon, you know, I will like it even if it's the same as usual...
Yes！ It's the same as usual.
Alright！ Then when should we do it？
Okay, from ▲月▲▲日▲, so our honeymoon lasts for two days and one night！
Ah, then... it's a honeymoon-themed trip to Hakone！
With that kind of theme, I wonder if we'll get along a little more than usual... I'm kidding.
(I did it！！ We'll be on a trip together to Hakone. Me and ▲高嶺＊＊▲！)
(I know！ I wonder if I should invite Makana to a trip to Hakone again.)
You know, I actually won a travel prize to our honeymoon again！
Umm, you know... it's a one-night, two-day trip to Hakone.
Ah, yes. T-That's what you meant, yes！
So, you mean, you're okay with it？
Yeah... it's good because it's like practice. No matter how many times we do it...
Alright！ Then when should we do it？
(Let's set the date day. Practice is important.)
Well then, from ▲月▲▲日▲, so our honeymoon lasts for two days and one night！
It's a honeymoon practice trip to Hakone！
Yes, let's get a lot of practice▼
(Yay！！ We'll go on a trip to Hakone, me and ▲高嶺＊＊▲！)
Well, it's about our trip, but you see, this time...
Yes, our honeym-- No, our trip to Hakone, right？
Yes. Why don't we go shopping？
It's okay, but... It's one night, right？ Do you need something specific？
Nothing like that. I was wondering if it's better to get some practice in that place...
(Practice？？？ Well, it's fine so let's go.)
Okay then... This is where we'll practice, right？
I was just thinking that if it was a real honeymoon, why don't we look for what we need？
Yes, I understand... Okay, let's go！
Alright, are you looking for something like this？
I wonder about that, but I found one I liked. One bag can become heavy with things from two people.
Yeah, you're right！ Is it the same as packing to go home as newlyweds？
Yes... And I'm sure we'll pack together like this in the future.
This practice was fun. I'm looking forward to our trip, more and more.
Yeah！ Then, shall we go back home？
Oh, I still have something to do... Can you go back first？
Are you going to do some real shopping？
Yes, my practice for shopping is not over yet.
Then, want me to go with you？
No, that's fine！ It's individual practice... Bye-bye.
(I'm sure she will look into bride stuff.)
(I wonder if you have arrived before me. Ah, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！)
Good morning！ Did I make you wait, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
It's already hot and humid in the mornings...
Hehe, it's June. Hey, how do you say June in Japanese？
...？ Isn't it something like "roku gatsu"？ Why？
Well, since it's June, you know something like that...
Ah, it's the June Bride month！
Ah, isn't it a little cold in the mornings？
Hmm, I'm sure Hakone is a little more cold. Besides, there will be autumn leaves.
A honeymoon among the autumn leaves！
It'll be good if that happens... Even if it's practice, it's nice to be romantic...
Alright, let's start our trip to Hakone, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
It's because it's my first time.
Your first time going to Hakone via this train？
Yes, it's a romancecar▼ When I went with my family, we went by car.
Ah, this is... Umm, a 30000-type EXE！
I see, it has that kind of shape.
Yup. It's a 6th gen, and it's the most common form used for commuting.
I see, I'm riding the EXE... Hehe♪
(This is not a honeymoon- like conversation.)
Are you looking forward to the "Romancecar" so much？
Umm, of course, not only that, but also Hakone...
Well, but riding the limited express is also fun！
That's right！ Are you looking forward to ride the "Romancecar"？♪
Yes, the 30000-type. Hey, let's ride it！
(You get so excited when it comes to trains ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
Really！ Hey, do you feel lonely？
The seat is wide, so we're a little far way, right？
But I'm not lonely, because I don't have an armrest♪ Hehe▼
Hmm... I like the limited express！
Yeah, even though the seats are wide, and I feel a little lonely！
Yes▼ You're not lonely anymore, right？ Hehe！
Ah, Mt. Fuji！ It looks a lot closer...
It's like that time at Atami...
Did you do it too when we traveled to Atami？ Pretending to be on a honeymoon, I mean.
This time... what are you going to do？ Because this is a practice trip...
What do you wanna do ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Did you do it when we traveled to Atami？ Pretending to be on a honeymoon, I mean.
Ah... you were referring to that.
But this trip is a form of "practice", and about it...
What do you wanna do ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Well then... I guess I'll "pretend" for now.
(It's a little embarrassing, but let's do our best.)
Perhaps we have been doing it since the time we went to Atami.
Hmm, if you think about it, you might be right.
Okay, let's practice a lot this time as well▼
We will soon arrive at the end point, Hakone Yumoto. For the Hakone Tozan Line and Gora...
Look, it's Hakone Yumoto. There are a few stops left, so it's closer.
Hah～！ We finally arrived at Hakone！
So many shops lined up all the time... It's amazing...
Okay, what should we do first？
Let's walk to the "Hydrangea Bridge" first.
Hmm... not that, I meant something related to our practice...
Ah, I see... So what then？
Hah～！ We've arrived in Hakone again！
When we arrived in Hakone, I remembered all the colors... from our last honeymoon.
Well then... Manaka, come with me？
(Even though it's been too long, I'm still embarrassed.)
The Hydrangea Bridge. You can clearly see Hayakawa...
Oh, there is a hydrangea by the riverbank...
In June, Hakone will entertain tourists throughout town.
And with that, can we see more of Hakone？
Yes, I'm sure it'll be fun▼
It's the "Hydrangea Bridge". Isn't the hydrangea blooming？
Hehe, yes. But, can you see it？ There are leaves instead...
A mountain of autumn leaves to give color to our honeymoon...
Yes, maybe we rediscovered it. A new way to enjoy honeymoon in Hakone.
I hope we can see a lot of autumn leaves in Hakone.
It's a little early, but let's eat lunch around this place.
Is there anything you want to eat？
Hmm... can we have soba？ Since we came all the way to Hakone.
Soba, huh. Okay, let's go find some！
Ah, how about we check around here？ Would you like to go there？ To "Hatsuhana".
Ah, it seems to have history behind it！
It's thriving with people... Is it a famous store？
Yes, it is. It was show on TV... Did you read the store description？
The soba here is kneaded with yam and eggs without using water.
Sorry to keep you waiting, here is your "Sadajo Soba" and your "Tempura Soba".
Oh！？ It's delicious！ What do you think ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
"Sadajo Soba", huh？ I wonder if I should order that...
Then... do you want to exchange dishes？
If we're newlyweds, isn't it natural to do it...？
Thank you for the food, it was delicious.
Shall we have lunch before going to the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum"？
Yeah, since we came to Hakone, why don't we go to "Hatsuhana" again？
You seriously like that place, don't you？ Alright, let's go ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
Wow, it looks like it's crowded today...
Sorry to keep you waiting. Here is your "Sadajo Soba" and your "Tendon".
Did you ask for the same dish from last time, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Certainly, it's delicious！ Yeah... I wonder if I should have done it too...
Geez, once again？ Then, want to try mine？
It's because my husband wants to eat it...
Next is the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum".
Then, we'll have to go to the Hakone Tozan Railway, right？ To Gora we go！
Ah, a 1000-type！ Umm... it's a Bernina！
I see！ So this vehicle has a name. You sure know your stuff...
I just happened to know it... I know, hey, can we go see the watering tank？
Hey, we're going to the Hakone Tozan Railway next, right？
Yes, to get to the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum" we have to go through Gora.
Hmm... When you told me about back then, it stuck.
Right？ I'm in your care again. Do your best, Bernina♪
80 per mile... Even though it's a train, it can go so fast...
That's... Yeah, it's definitely amazing. Look, the hydrangea is also beautiful, right？
It really is, a lot of flowers are in bloom... I'm glad we came in a good season.
Ah, look！ It's almost time to switch trains！
Hey, you can see the autumn leaves when you climb the mountain by train, right？
Sure. Hey, what is that thing？
In case of emergency, we need a rail crimping brake...
We arrived！ The last stop, Gora station！
Wow... it's a little cold after all.
It's a mountain railway, right？ Look, the station building looks like a mountain lodge.
You're right！ Now then, let's go to "Hakone Glass Forest Museum".
Yes. We have to take a bus, right？
Yes. Do you hate buses, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Can you say to me "Come with me"？
We arrived！ The last stop, Gora Station！
Ugh, it's a little cold and the wind is a little strong.
It seems that there used to be an outdoor skating ring...
Now we have to take a bus to "Hakone Glass Forest Museum", right？
I know, do you want to take a break？
I'm alright. Now, if you do it...
We'll get there very soon, do your best, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
Okay. I'm glad to be together with my gentle husband.
Did it look like it was shaking？
Next stop is Tawarashi/ Hakone Glass Forest...
We have arrived to Hakone Forest Glass Museum. Customers who get off should not forget anything...
"Hakone Glass Forest Museum". It's right here.
Wow... It's made of stone and looks like a real old castle.
And see over there！ A glass tree！
It's glittering！ I see, it's a glass forest！
Please take your time and enjoy.
Look at this ticket！ It has an interesting shape.
We have arrived to Hakone Forest Glass Museum. Customers who get off should not forget anything...
We arrived at the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum"！
The glass tree is so beautiful today...
Even if you know that's the reflection of the sun, it's mysterious...
Please take your time and enjoy.
Did you notice？ The ticket changed compared to last time. Does it change depending on the season？
It seems so. It's still too elaborated, though...
It's beautiful... The whole building seems like the exact image of Venice.
Speaking of which, the Venetian flag is at the entrance... But it's glittering, and more――
Do you promise you won't laugh？
It's like a fairy tail world. Look, it's like the princess and prince are coming out.
It's a hydrangea made of glass...
It's called "Hortensia" and it's made up to 2,000 pieces of glass.
Hehe！ Hey, did you see it？ There are many other hydrangeas in bloom！
Oh, the grass of glass is...
Yes... one hundred pieces of glass... 100 pieces！？
It's autumn in the country of glass. Hehe♪
A corridor of light... Crystal glass, let's see... 160,000 parts！？
Hehe, it's swaying with the wind and glittering, it's beautiful...
Do you want to take a photo？
Hey, when you pass through, you're supposed to be a prince and a princess, right？
You're fine as the princess, but should I be the prince？
Well then... Shall we go visit, princess？
Do you like what you see here ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
It's because... This is what you see at the end of fairy tail stories, right？
Something like "And they lived happily forever."
I imagined it since I as little. "Where will you live in the future？", I asked myself.
Did you imagine this kind of place？
It's called "Hortensia", and it says it uses 2,000 pieces of glass.
Hehe！ Hey, did you see？ There are many other hydrangeas in bloom！
It's autumn in the country of class. Hehe♪
It's shining today too... It's dazzling.
Do you want to take a photo？
Hey, can we do it again？
Okay then... Shall we go visit, my princess？
Look, a chandelier！ It's like a castle hall！
It looks fine！ Is that a "Millefiori"？
It seems to mean something like "a thousand flowers". It's a mosaic glass technique from ancient Rome.
Stretching the glass out, making patterns smaller and smaller... It's amazing...
A "Globe with dot-colored flower lid". It looks like from around the 16th century...
I wonder if I can put something in and drink from it...
With this？ It looks heavy, but... Ah, look at it from behind――
The light coming from it is cobalt blue. It's beautiful...
And over here... Is this the museum shop？
Wow！ Can we take a look？
Do you want to take a look？
There seems to be various things... Ah, is that a "Millefiori"？
It's like combining glasses and melting them together. It sounds interesting...
Yay... Hmm, is this really beautiful？
It took about 70 minutes to make.
Want to take a break at the restaurant？
It's the "Cafe Terrazza". It's amazing！ It even has live music.
Hehe, is it called "Canzone"？ It feels like we're in Italy, right？
Sorry to keep you waiting. Here is your fruit tea.
Wow, this has lots of fruits！
There is plenty for two people！
Okay, can you lend me a cup？ We'll have a drink together？ Right, Dear▼
Here, sorry to keep you waiting. It has a very beautiful finish, right？
Thank you very much. Oh, it's so beautiful.
We still have some time left so, want to look around a little more？
Look, a glass fountain！ Fontana, huh...
Oh... There are 45,000 glass pieces. I'm not surprised anymore.
Hehe！ Ah, hey, over there. Huh, what is that？
Like the one in Cape Aijo？
There seems to be no explanation in particular...
It's like a bell to ring together. Hey, can we ring it？
But, what wish can we make on it？
(Then, what I will wish for with ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
What did you wish for ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Umm... It's a secret. But I'm sure it's the same as yours.
Yeah, this is a real honeymoon after all...
Look, it's the Fontana！ The Glass Fountain！ It's glittering.
I know, do you want to ring the "Oath Bell"？
Yes, I also want to make a wish again. Hehe！
(Okay, what I will wish for with ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
Hey, do you want to do something new tomorrow？
We had so much fun in the Glass Forest...
Did you like it that much ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes... When I was there, I felt like one of my childhood dreams had come true.
I see. I'm glad for you.
The bus has arrived, let's go！
Are you okay going by bus？
I'm fine, I was just thinking a little.
I wonder if a true honeymoon is happier that this. I can't imagine it...
Next is the end point, Togendai, Togendai. Hakone Ropeway, the sea...
Wow, I can see Lake Ashi！
We're going to board a ship tomorrow, right？ A pirate ship！
Yes, today we're just staying at the hotel, though.
It's nothing... I just remembered that we're newlyweds.
(When you say that, I get kinda nervous.)
Hey, you can see it from here！ The "Hakone Lake Hotel"！
Ah, I see. Well then... Manaka, come with me.
We arrived at the "Hakone Lake Hotel"！
Wow... It looks like a foreign hotel... There is also a large chandelier.
It'll be okay... I'll just go check-in.
Maybe we can use the same last name, you know, like practice since we're here together...
Sorry for the delay. I think I wrote it right, “▲苗字▲ Manaka”, like this.
Sorry to keep you waiting. Now then, I will explain the facilities we have in the hall.
Please come here with your wife.
Hehe, we arrived to the hotel again, right？
That's right, I'll go check-us in.
Hey, what did you write as my name...
Did I write it wrong？ It's “▲苗字▲ Manaka”, like last time.
It's something that feels so nice...
Sorry to keep you waiting. Then, I will explain the facilities we have in the hall.
Please come here with your wife.
I wonder if I did it well... I'm kidding.
I'm glad. To tell you the truth, I was a little nervous...
We can relax on the tatami mats！
Yes, hehe！ Oh, you can see the mountains very close from this window！
It's true. Well then, should we lay out the futons ourselves？
The futon... Ah, yeah, I'll do it... It's for practice.
I was thinking this is nice.
My house doesn't have Japanese-style rooms, so I like this kind of thing.
With a small table, brewing tea with my husband... I would really like that.
We still have some time left... Do you want to take a bath first？
The men's bath is "heaven" and women's bath is "sky"... Oh, there is an open-air bath！
As newlyweds, we should go in together...
Geez, then, I'll meet you at the lobby, okay？
The open-air bath is so good！..
Is there an object like this too？ Emm, it looks like a cocoon...
Cocoon？ Ah, it's over here too！
What is that？ It has light inside it... Hey, I'll check it out！
Hello～～o. I come to make my report～. It was a sauna～.
There is light inside, it's very fashionable.
I see！ Would you like to go in？
Hah～... The hot water was so good.
(You're still inside the bath I suppose, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
Don't look at me too much...
Geez... Hey, can we take a walk back to the hotel？
Okay then... Huh, you know what to do.
I see, there's even a relaxation room.
I want to enter！ Can I？
Hah～... We ended up feeling fluffier. Hehe♪
It didn't work for me... Then, next――
A souvenir corner！ Hey, can we go in？
Is that a Hakone specialty？ There are lots of things...
Those parquets look so beautiful！ It's so nice...
Do you want to buy sweets？
Ah, sure. Gotoji themed？ Also manjuus, and some cookies...
Hey, are you hungry？ Do you want to eat something？
Did you get hungry when you saw the sweets？
It's because... You're so mean, my husband.
Wow... This place gives out an adult-like feeling, doesn't it？
Sorry to keep you waiting. Here you have your "Sanzoku-yaki made of pork loin".
Really. But, I'm not that hungry...
Did you eat too much before ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes, I had more than enough...
Then, do you want me to help with your share？
Please, eat a lot my husband？ Okay, open wide▼
Thank you so much for the food. I'm so full...
Are you okay？ I'm sure I did eat my share...
I'm fine, I'll just take a break.
Then, can you lie down？ I'll give you a massage. Ah, but a while ago――
No, no！ By all means, please.
Hehe♪ Hmm～～, I'm good at this... Then, how's this？ *Rub, rub*♪
Your massages are so good ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
Can I be a good wife now？ Hehe！
Ah... Hey, why don't we go see the lake before it's late？
You're right, we haven't gone there. Let's go！
Oh, it's night already, right？ Ah, the hotel...
Yeah, it looks really nice... Hey, shall we go？
Yes... Even then, you can see the lights outside, and those are beautiful.
Hey, in this case, what is a good topic to talk about？
And this is about the future: What would you like to have, a boy or a girl？
I like... Hmmm, both actually. And as many as possible.
Yes, getting up early every morning, making breakfast and waking you and the children...
Hehe, then can you help me？
I like to be always with my family. Everyone eating breakfast, and taking baths...
I like that, it sounds good...
So when the kids go to bed, I'll go back with my lover. Just like now...
It's night already... Hey, shall we go？
Well ride it again tomorrow, right？
When I went to see the front, I saw a papa and mama with lots of kids.
Both of them were hugging a baby, and were holding the hands of the little kids.
Eh？ Umm, can you imagine it？
Hehe, I did imagine it. You where holding the hand of a little kid.
You would be a nice Papa, right？ I'm sure Mama will be happy... I'm kidding.
Even if we become Papa and Mama, let's always do this, okay？
There is a promenade over there...
Eh, right now！？ Shouldn't we stop？ It's dark, isn't it dangerous？
It's even more dark than I imagined...
It feels like it wouldn't be strange if something came out of that bush...
Ah, the promenade！.. Do you want to go in？
It's because you're trying to scare me...
I won't do that！ Come with me, Manaka？
In movies, a man with an axe suddenly pops out from the sides, right？
It's alright, it's only the tree branches！
Geez, meanie！ Don't be like that my husband！
Now then... It's too early to go to bed, should we lay down the futon first？
Ah, then should I lay them out？
No, it's for practice. It's a wife's job, right？
No, no, it's hard work. I'll do it！
Hey... I feel like our futons are closer...
I see... You think so？ You know, we're newly married！
Can I take a bath again？
I was sweating when we were walking outside.
It was cold around the lake, so I wanted to sleep a little after warming up.
(Fuh... don't get me wrong, it's practice for our honeymoon.)
Well, then I'll see you later, okay？
Can I enter the sauna？ Do you think it's fine even at this hour？
Okay！ Then, can I go with you？
Ah, it feels good... Hah～, I'm in heaven...
I had a dream！！ I was really going to heaven...
What's wrong？ You were taking too long in the bath.
Aren't you dazed？ Your face looks a little red...
(I should stop taking naps in the hot springs.)
(I don't have anything else to do, I go to sleep. ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is...)
Shall we go to bed soon？ Isn't it time to finish practicing？
I sometimes think that my way of thinking is old...
But, if you feel the same... Then, I'm happy.
I love you because you're so kind.
Hey, can we talk after getting into the futon？
(Okay... We don't have anything else to do, I'll just turn off the lights and go to bed.)
Are you going to sleep？ Isn't it time to finish practicing？
I wanted a goodnight kiss. I'm kidding... Hehe▼
I wonder if she's sleeping well.
(I'm glad I got up early, because I slept properly yesterday！)
Hehe♪ You're sleeping well～ It's almost time for breakfast～
Hmm, I feel a little sorry for this... Here it goes～
Here it goes, ready？ Tickle attack～！
This is also a wife's duty. Did you sleep well？ Dear▼
(This is a nice way to wake up.)
Geez... you did that on purpose, pervert...
Breakfast will be served soon. Please change your clothes soon, my husband.
It's alright... Sorry to keep you waiting, it's okay now.
Breakfast will be served soon. Please change your clothes soon, my husband.
Huh？ Wait a minute！ Let me turn around！
Ah... the scent of freshly baked bread...
Oh, this is a lot of food.
Did you also take a lot, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
It's all good♪ You have to eat a lot in the morning. Don't we have a lot of things to do today？
Hey, having breakfast on a terrace like this, you know...
It's like being on a honeymoon？
Yes, I was longing for it.
I see, I'm glad you feel like it. Okay, let's eat.
Okay！ Then, since we're newlyweds, open wide▼
Thank you for choosing us. We look forward to seeing you again.
Alright... We didn't forget anything, right？
The "Hakone Lake Hotel" is truly a comfortable hotel.
Yes, I hope we can come again... Hey, why don't we take a photo？
Good！ Then, we'll go to Owakudani's ropeway right now！
Sorry to keep you waiting！ I bought the tickets.
Thank you. Hey, huh, did you see that？
Look, there are two ropes. We're going on that rope...
It's nice, it's such a big machine...
Don't admire the place... C'mon, let's line up！
Did you wait too much？ I was buying the tickets.
It's such a nice weather today. We can enjoy a walk in the sky！
Ah, I see... You're not good with heights？... Are you okay？
I'm fine. My husband is with me, I'm kidding.
Smoke is coming out from the ground！ Look, can you see it！
...You're not looking well, are you okay？
I-I'm fine. It really is beautiful... I'm kidding.
You're not doing fine in high places... Manaka, come with me.
Thank you. I'm glad I have a reliable husband▼
Soon, we will arrive at Owakudani Station. The rope to Sounzan will...
Oh... it's a wonderful view... Are you okay, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
If I do this, I'll be fine.
Hey, can you see it？ Mt. Fuji looks so big...
Soon, we will arrive at Owakudani Station. The rope to Sounzan will...
We arrived... Oh, so this is Owakudani！！
Amazing... I think this place was used to be called Jigokudani...
Yes, it's amazing. Does it smell like hydrogen sulfide？
You add hydrochloric acid to iron sulfide, right？ Didn't you try it as an experiment in junior high？
The hot springs are carried by steel pipes with a total length of 2600m, with a height difference of 350m...
Oh～！ I see. Would you like to see more？
Amazing... A lot of smoke is coming from the ground. It's an active volcano...
Hehe, it's nice♪ Let's hurry up！
Yes, hydrogen sulfide reacts with iron to form iron sulfide... That's how black egg's are made...
(This seems more like a chemistry class.)
The steam is amazing... It can keep boiling water at 80 degrees Celsius...
You need 1 cal to raise 1 cc of water at once, right？ That means...
How much heat will it have？ After all――
Um... Would you like to go see other places？
Show it to me！ Oh, it really is black！ Amazing！
I wonder if it has iron sulfide.
...Hmm？ Well, maybe... No matter how it looks――
Alright, let's eat！ It's hot, so be careful.
Yes... I'm nervous, but also relieved to do this...
This is what a honeymoon is like... I'm kidding▼
Soon, we will arrive at Togendai Station. Hakone Pirate Ship, Hakone Town...
It's a little early, but can we have lunch here before boarding the pirate ship？
Okay. Want to do it near a place facing the lake？
Oh... There are various menus！ Which one do you want？
Me？ Emm, well then... Hmm？ Huh！ This one！
Ginger saute. The pork looks delicious.
I see... Looks like a kind of special pig. It really looks delicious.
Is it that good？ Can you eat it all？
Can you help me？ I can't eat it all. Okay, say ah♪
Today I'll have a cutlet curry, with salad.
Are you sure you want to have cutlet curry？
